### 2. Biochemistry Monomer Structures

#### Phosphate & Sugars (DNA/RNA Backbone)
* Phosphate Ion: HO-P(=O)(OH)-O⁻ / PO4³⁻ derivative linked via phosphodiester bonds.
* Glucose: C6H12O6 (Hexose monomer ring structure).
* 2-deoxyribose: C5H10O4 (Pentose sugar component of DNA nucleotides, missing an -OH at position 2).

#### Nitrogenous Bases
* Adenine (A): Purine base (C5H5N5) with an amine group (-NH2) at position 6.
* Guanine (G): Purine base (C5H5N5O) with a carbonyl at position 6 and amine at position 2.
* Cytosine (C): Pyrimidine base (C4H5N3O) with a carbonyl at position 2 and amine at position 4.
* Thymine (T): Pyrimidine base (C5H6N2O2) with carbonyls at positions 2 and 4, and a methyl group (-CH3) at position 5.

#### Amino Acids (H2N-CH(R)-COOH)
* Alanine: R = -CH3
* Aspartic Acid: R = -CH2COOH
* Cysteine: R = -CH2SH
* Lysine: R = -CH2CH2CH2CH2NH2
* Phenylalanine: R = -CH2C6H5 (Benzyl sidechain)
* Serine: R = -CH2OH

