### 3. Complex Macrocyclic Systems

#### Haem B Structure
* Central Core: Iron(II) ion (Fe²⁺) co-ordinately bonded in a planar configuration.
* Ligand System: Tetradentate porphyrin ring consisting of 4 pyrrole rings linked by methene (=CH-) bridges.
* Substituents on Ring Peripheral: 4 methyl groups (-CH3), 2 vinyl groups (-CH=CH2), and 2 propanoic acid sidechains (-CH2CH2COOH).
* Function: Forms a coordinate bond to O2 in haemoglobin; easily displaced by carbon monoxide (CO) due to competitive ligand substitution.
